doc_summary_long: Venezuela Erupts In 'Mother Of All Protests' As Anti-Maduro Sentiment Seethes. Racked by food shortages and political unrest, Venezuela swelled with what organizers are calling the 'mother of all protests' on Wednesday. Demonstrators have taken to the streets in the capital, Caracas, and other major cities across the country to rally against the government of President Nicolas Maduro, who assumed office precisely five years ago.
doc_summary_short: Venezuela Erupts In 'Mother Of All Protests' As Anti-Maduro Sentiment Seethes.
